      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the student loan statement, a parchment of ancient wisdom, much like the scrolls of old that the wise and ancient wizards used to keep track of their magical expenses. Now, imagine your student loan as a mischievous goblin hoarding gold coins. Each month, you give the goblin a pouch of coins, but the goblin, being a sly creature, takes a small portion of your pouch to add to his hoard. This portion is the interest, my friend, and it grows over time, much like a goblin's treasure pile.\n\nThe principal, the original amount you borrowed, is like the goblin's initial stash of gold. As you continue to give the goblin your monthly pouch, a part of it goes towards the goblin's hoard (interest), and the rest goes towards reducing the goblin's stash (principal). The goblin's hoard grows slowly, but the goblin is clever and always finds a way to make it seem like the goblin's stash is growing faster than it actually is.\n\nSo, when you see that the amount you owe isn't going down as much as you expected, it's because the goblin's hoard (interest) is growing faster than the gob",
